West wall:<br>
Single person who knows what they are doing running in: 0-1 adds<br>
1 group of lvl 60ish people: 1-2 adds<br>
3+ groups of people: 3+ adds<br>
<br>
North wall:<br>
Single person who knows what they are doing running in: 0-1 adds<br>
1 group of lvl 60ish people: 2-4 adds<br>
3+ groups of people: the entire fricking side of the zone.<br>
<br>
North wall breaks, imho, are silly, slow, and unnecessary.<br>
I actually agree with the origional poster, best break is a group of 6 who know what htey are doing hitting the west wall...then you can pull the portal area and the rest of the raid can waltz in in 10-20 minutes.<br>
<br>
As for AE, well, it works, just has decently still class requirements...also, the ae groups had better be experienced.<br>
