<br>
Siegert:<br>
The whole Dread problem is this: There are a few mobs just north and slightly east of the zin hill (near the Tent Tormenter bridge), that, when they agro, path badly, running back into the center of the zone (as a monk im sure youve seen the way mobs dont like running under the TT bridge? well if you run too fast, they run back towards Dread...and so agroing Dread, so getting you DTed) (and I HATE that stupid bug).<br>
<br>
For those that might be wondering, the west wall break takes place just north of teh ledge basically....almost directly west of the zin hill for several reasons:<br>
THere are no static spawns that will agro from there.<br>
There are few see invis mobs there.<br>
The warping for those that lag a bit is better than the ledge.<br>
The pathing is reasonably straightfoward there.<br>
Less chance of agroing the scarelings around that yellow pillar near the SW corner.<br>
Also, there are less wanderers than in most parts of the zone.<br>
<br>
CR's can be tricky there...just as with anywhere in fear (They added at least 2 wanderers that patrol through the North camp..or at least, they did...i havent done a North wall break in a LONG time)....but if you have one clothed 60 druid or ranger, or 2 naked ones...you should be able to get in and control the one or two adds you get while you rez.<br>
<br>
Also....as with any other break in....have an abort plan if possible....take a druid or wiz in (im partial to a druid..for obvious reasons), and if things get tight, evac...thats why you break with one group...less agro, easier escape.<br>
<br>
Kendaien<br>
